### Step 5: Understand isolated context

Look at `synthesis_subagent`. It receives `all_findings` as a parameter — it has no way to "remember" what search or analysis found in prior calls. If the coordinator forgot to pass search results, synthesis would operate on analysis results alone.

This is why Step 3 of the coordinator explicitly collects all findings into `all_findings` and passes the complete list. In production, this means the synthesis agent's prompt includes the full text of all prior findings — not a summary, not a reference, but the actual data.

