```

The YAML frontmatter fields:
- `name` — identifier for the subagent
- `description` — what the coordinator sees when selecting subagents
- `tools` — comma-separated list, scoped to this subagent's role
- `model` — `sonnet`, `opus`, `haiku`, or `inherit` from parent

The body becomes the subagent's system prompt. This is equivalent to the `AgentDefinition` in Step 6 of the Python script, but configured as a file instead of code.

### Step 8: Verify source traceability

Look at Part 6 of the script output. Every finding in the pipeline has a `source` field. If any step strips this field — passing a summary instead of the full handoff — the final report loses traceability.

The test: for every claim in the synthesis output, can you trace it back to a specific source URL or document name? If yes, the handoff format is working. If not, something was lost in transit.

