**Correct: C.** The descriptions say the same thing -- "Searches records and returns matching entries" gives Claude no signal to prefer one over the other. Adding Use-for and Do-NOT-use-for draws the boundary between CRM requests and payment requests. A routing classifier (A) patches the symptom and adds a new failure point; fix descriptions first. Renaming (B) clarifies the names but the descriptions are still identical -- Claude reads the description, not just the name. Few-shot examples (D) improve token-weighted probability but are a heavier intervention than simply clarifying the descriptions, which is the direct fix.

