**Q2.** Your system prompt says: "You are an assistant that specializes in document review and analysis." One of your tools is named `extract_document_data`. What is the risk?

**A.** Claude will refuse to call any tool not mentioned by name in the system prompt
**B.** The word "document" in the system prompt biases Claude toward `extract_document_data` even when the request does not involve a document
**C.** The system prompt will override the tool's input schema, causing validation errors
**D.** System prompts have no effect on tool selection -- only tool descriptions matter

**Correct: B.** Claude reads the system prompt as context for every decision, including tool selection. A word that appears in both the system prompt and a tool name creates selection bias. Claude does not refuse to call unlisted tools (A), system prompts do not override schemas (C), and system prompts absolutely do affect tool selection because they shape the entire context Claude reasons within (D is wrong).

