## Check your understanding

**Q1.** Your extraction pipeline uses `tool_choice: "auto"`. It works 85% of the time but crashes 15% of the time because Claude returns a text summary instead of calling the extraction tool. What is the correct fix?

**A.** Improve the extraction tool's description so Claude picks it more reliably with `"auto"`
**B.** Set `tool_choice` to `"any"` so Claude must call a tool, guaranteeing structured output
**C.** Add retry logic: if the response is text, re-send the request
**D.** Increase `max_tokens` so Claude has room to return both text and a tool call

**Correct: B.** `"any"` forces a tool call -- Claude must call one of the available tools, eliminating text-only responses that crash the parser. **Why not A:** Better descriptions improve tool selection accuracy but don't eliminate text-only responses -- `"auto"` can always return text regardless of description quality. **Why not C:** Retry is probabilistic -- the second request may also return text, creating a retry loop with no guarantee of success. **Why not D:** `max_tokens` controls output length, not whether Claude calls a tool versus returning text.

